FBIS4-65642 "drweu098_p_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-098 Daily Report 19 May 1994 GREECE Clarification of U.S. Military Aid Proviso Clarification of U.S. Military Aid Proviso NC1905132594 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in Greek 1130 GMT 19 May 94 NC1905132594 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network Greek BFN [Text] Greece has not been accused of violating the embargo on Serbia and Montenegro, according to the Foreign Ministry. While the U.S. House of Representatives is safeguarding the 7:10 ratio in military aid to Greece and Turkey, according to a proposal, it must first be established that the embargo is not being violated. The Greek Government, the Foreign Ministry says, has taken all the necessary measures to maintain the sanctions against Serbia and Montenegro. Government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos noted that Greece and Serbia have no joint territorial border. He reiterated that Greece is not violating the embargo against Serbia and Montenegro and noted that the 7:10 ratio in U.S. aid to Greece and Turkey continues.
